---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Job Search — Technical PM Roles (Feb 24)">
  <main>
    <h1>🔍 Technical PM Roles — Feb 24, 2026</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Focus: Technical Product Manager / Senior PM at tech companies. London, UK-remote, or EU-remote. Ranked by fit (10 = perfect).</p>

    <div class="job" id="decagon">
      <div class="rank rank-9">9/10</div>
      <h2>Decagon — Senior Agent Product Manager</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 AI Agents (conversational AI) | 💰 Series B, $100M+ raised (Accel, a16z, Bain)</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> AI agent platform, PM role that involves writing prompt logic, designing product features, AND working with customers' executive teams on AI roadmaps. They want "ex-founders and aspiring founders". This is the Cloudflare role but actually in London.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> 4+ years relevant experience (PM, consultant, founder). Technical enough to write and test prompt logic. Customer-facing.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/decagon/dcf9b561-f2fb-422b-88a9-33ce76e96608" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://decagon.ai" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="hopper">
      <div class="rank rank-9">9/10</div>
      <h2>Hopper — Sr PM, Commerce - AI & Platform (100% Remote UK)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 Remote UK | 🏢 Travel tech (B2B e-commerce) | 💰 $750M+ raised, profitable</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Greenfield 0-to-1 role. Lead AI strategy for B2B platform. Own APIs, LLM integration, partner tools. "Highly technical" and "high autonomy" in the JD. They want someone who can define architecture AND talk to partners. Marketplace experience is a huge plus (Hire Space!).</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Technical PM with API/platform experience. Data-driven. Entrepreneurial mindset.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/hopper/935e0c08-4c14-44ca-82a6-9345f2145979" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.hopper.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="devrev">
      <div class="rank rank-8">8/10</div>
      <h2>DevRev — Senior Product Manager, Voice</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 AI workspace / CRM | 💰 Series A, Khosla Ventures backed</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> AI-native company building "Computer" (AI workspace). This PM role owns Voice as an input modality into their agent ecosystem: Memory, AirSync, Agents. Very technical, very AI-native. Founded by Dheeraj Pandey (ex-Nutanix CEO, $5B company).</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> PM experience with voice/conversational AI. Understanding of LLMs and agent architectures.</p>
      <a href="https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/devrev/jobs/5742282004" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://devrev.ai" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="spotify">
      <div class="rank rank-7">7/10</div>
      <h2>Spotify — Senior PM, Content Platform</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 Music/podcasts streaming | 💰 Public (NYSE: SPOT)</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Content Platform is the engine processing Spotify's entire catalog: ingestion, processing, delivery to 600M+ users. Serious scale, technical PM role. Not AI-specific but deeply technical platform work at one of the best product orgs in Europe.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Senior PM. Experience with platform/infrastructure products. Data pipelines at scale.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.lever.co/spotify/28cd347f-d5dd-4cf0-84bd-48f424b8d8d3" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.spotify.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="algolia">
      <div class="rank rank-8">8/10</div>
      <h2>Algolia — Senior PM, AI Search + Senior PM, Data</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 Search/discovery APIs | 💰 $334M raised, Series D</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Developer-facing API company (1.5 trillion searches/year). Two roles open in London: AI Search and Data Platform. Both are deeply technical, API-focused, and directly in the AI/ML space. Perfect for a PM who understands both developer experience and enterprise needs.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> API product experience. Search/ML background a plus. B2B SaaS.</p>
      <a href="https://job-boards.greenhouse.io/algolia/jobs/5725185004" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply → (Data)</a>
      <a href="https://www.algolia.com/careers" target="_blank" class="company-link">All roles ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="sparta">
      <div class="rank rank-7">7/10</div>
      <h2>Sparta Commodities — Technical Product Manager</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London / Madrid / Barcelona | 🏢 Commodity trading platform | 💰 Series B, $46M raised</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Technical PM at a fast-growing trading platform. London OR Madrid base (nice flexibility). Data-heavy, technical product. Swiss company with strong engineering culture.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Technical PM experience. Trading/fintech a plus but not required.</p>
      <a href="https://uk.linkedin.com/jobs/view/technical-product-manager-based-london-madrid-or-barcelona-at-sparta-4159048192" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.spartacommodities.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="mapbox">
      <div class="rank rank-7">7/10</div>
      <h2>Mapbox — Principal Product Manager, Navigation</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London / US | 🏢 Location/mapping platform | 💰 $427M raised</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Developer-facing platform (4M+ registered devs). Principal PM = strategic + hands-on. Navigation is their core revenue driver. Technical, API-heavy, B2B/B2D company.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Senior/principal level. Platform product experience. Customer-facing.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/mapbox/6c12e8db-464e-42d5-8b83-2e4016f7b74d" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.mapbox.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="isomorphic">
      <div class="rank rank-6">6/10</div>
      <h2>Isomorphic Labs — Product Manager</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 AI drug discovery (Alphabet/DeepMind spinoff) | 💰 Alphabet-funded</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Cutting-edge AI company from the AlphaFold team. PM role focused on data strategy. Prestigious, deeply technical. Lower fit score because it's bio/pharma domain-specific and less "builder" culture.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> PM experience. Data/ML platform understanding. Bio/pharma a plus.</p>
      <a href="https://app.welcometothejungle.com/jobs/M0ZHQzdW" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.isomorphiclabs.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="cryptio">
      <div class="rank rank-7">7/10</div>
      <h2>Cryptio — Senior PM (API & AI Platform)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 Crypto accounting/compliance | 💰 Series A, $30M raised</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Building developer-facing platforms with LLM/agentic systems interacting with APIs. JD specifically mentions "understanding of how LLMs and agentic systems interact with APIs". Very aligned with your AI agent interests. Crypto domain (you said it bores you, but the role itself is pure tech PM).</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Developer platform experience. API products. Fintech/crypto a plus.</p>
      <a href="https://uk.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-product-manager-api-ai-platform-at-cryptio" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://cryptio.co" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="permutive">
      <div class="rank rank-6">6/10</div>
      <h2>Permutive — Senior PM, Identity & Marketplace</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 Privacy-first ad tech | 💰 Series C, $75M raised</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Marketplace product (identity + data collaboration). Connected marketplace experience maps directly from Hire Space. Ad tech is niche but the marketplace PM skills are transferable.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Marketplace product experience. B2B platform. Data/privacy understanding.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/permutive/0e864bf6-bedf-49f3-a454-b52eba8fcd9b" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://permutive.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="depop">
      <div class="rank rank-6">6/10</div>
      <h2>Depop — Senior Product Manager (Trust & Safety)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 Remote UK (London 1x/month) | 🏢 Fashion marketplace | 💰 Acquired by Etsy ($1.6B)</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Marketplace PM role at a well-known consumer product. Also hiring PM for Search Retrieval (ML/AI). Marketplace scaling experience from Hire Space transfers well. Etsy backing = stability.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> PM experience. Marketplace understanding. Trust/safety or search depending on role.</p>
      <a href="https://depopcareers.com/careers/743999899294433" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.depop.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="cosine">
      <div class="rank rank-8">8/10</div>
      <h2>Cosine — Product Engineer (FullStack JS/TS)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 AI coding agents | 💰 YC-backed, $7M seed</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Not a PM title but a product-engineer role building developer workflow tools with AI. YC-backed, London, tiny team. "Product Engineer" is exactly the PM-who-codes profile. £60-120K. Included because it's the closest thing to the Cloudflare spirit role in London.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> FullStack JS/TS. Product thinking. AI/LLM experience.</p>
      <a href="https://www.ycombinator.com/companies/cosine/jobs" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://cosine.sh" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="datasite">
      <div class="rank rank-6">6/10</div>
      <h2>Datasite — Senior PM, Apps, Productivity Tools & AI Platform</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 London | 🏢 M&A deal platform | 💰 Private equity-backed, profitable</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> AI platform PM at a profitable B2B SaaS company. Not a startup but the AI platform work is genuinely interesting (Blueflame AI acquisition). Stable, London-based, enterprise product.</p>
      <p><strong>Requirements:</strong> Senior PM. AI/ML platform experience. Enterprise SaaS.</p>
      <a href="https://datasite.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/datasite/job/gbr---london/senior-product-manager---growth---plg_r36004" target="_blank" class="apply">Apply →</a>
      <a href="https://www.datasite.com" target="_blank" class="company-link">Company ↗</a>
    </div>

    <h2 class="section-header">🌍 Previously Identified (EU, from earlier research)</h2>

    <div class="job" id="n8n">
      <div class="rank rank-7">7/10</div>
      <h2>n8n — (No PM role open, but watch)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 Berlin / Remote EU | 🏢 AI workflow automation | 💰 $240M raised, $2.5B val</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> "The default tool for AI apps". Builder culture, remote-EU. No PM role right now but they're in hyper-growth post-Series C. Worth watching and making contact.</p>
      <a href="https://n8n.io/careers" target="_blank" class="company-link">Careers ↗</a>
    </div>

    <div class="job" id="dust">
      <div class="rank rank-8">8/10</div>
      <h2>Dust — (Reapproach)</h2>
      <div class="meta">📍 Paris | 🏢 AI agent platform for enterprises | 💰 Sequoia-backed</div>
      <p><strong>Why it fits:</strong> Exactly your thing: AI agent platform, developer-facing, small team. Already contacted them before but no formal application. Worth a proper approach.</p>
      <a href="https://jobs.ashbyhq.com/dust" target="_blank" class="company-link">Careers ↗</a>
    </div>

    <hr />
    <p class="footer">Compiled by Rook • Feb 24, 2026 • Sources: LinkedIn, Greenhouse, Ashby, Lever, company career pages, Brave Search</p>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  main {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    color: #e0e0e0;
    background: #0d1117;
  }
  h1 {
    font-size: 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.3rem;
  }
  .subtitle {
    color: #8b949e;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }
  .section-header {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #30363d;
  }
  .job {
    background: #161b22;
    border: 1px solid #30363d;
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .job h2 {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
    color: #f0f6fc;
  }
  .meta {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: #8b949e;
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }
  .job p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0.4rem 0;
  }
  .rank {
    position: absolute;
    top: 1rem;
    right: 1rem;
    font-weight: bold;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .rank-9 { background: #238636; color: #fff; }
  .rank-8 { background: #1f6feb; color: #fff; }
  .rank-7 { background: #6e40c9; color: #fff; }
  .rank-6 { background: #8b949e; color: #fff; }
  .apply {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    margin-right: 0.8rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
    background: #238636;
    color: #fff;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .apply:hover { background: #2ea043; }
  .company-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    padding: 0.4rem 1rem;
    background: #21262d;
    color: #58a6ff;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }
  .company-link:hover { background: #30363d; }
  hr {
    border: none;
    border-top: 1px solid #30363d;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }
  .footer {
    color: #484f58;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
